Python program that matches the specification and passes all tests.\n\n### Question:\nGiven a 0-indexed integer array nums of size n and two integers lower and upper, return the number of fair pairs.\nA pair (i, j) is fair if:\n\n0 <= i < j < n, and\nlower <= nums[i] + nums[j] <= upper\n\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [0,1,7,4,4,5], lower = 3, upper = 6\nOutput: 6\nExplanation: There are 6 fair pairs: (0,3), (0,4), (0,5), (1,3), (1,4), and (1,5).\n\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [1,7,9,2,5], lower = 11, upper = 11\nOutput: 1\nExplanation: There is a single fair pair: (2,3).\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 105\nnums.length == n\n-109 <= nums[i] <= 109\n-109 <= lower <= upper <= 109\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def countFairPairs(self, nums: List[int], lower: int, upper: int) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\nfrom bisect import bisect_left, bisect_right\n\nclass Solution:\n    def countFairPairs(self, nums: List[int], lower: int, upper: int) -> int:\n        nums.sort()\n        n = len(nums)\n        count = 0\n        \n        for i in range(n):\n            # Find the range of indices for valid j such that lower <= nums[i] + nums[j] <= upper\n            left_bound = lower - nums[i]\n            right_bound = upper - nums[i]\n            \n            # Find the first index where nums[j] >= left_bound\n            left_index = bisect_left(nums, left_bound, i + 1, n)\n            # Find the last index where nums[j] <= right_bound\n            right_index = bisect_right(nums, right_bound, i + 1, n) - 1\n            \n            # All indices from left_index to right_index are valid for j\n            if left_index <= right_index:\n                count += right_index - left_index + 1\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution sorts the array first, which allows us to efficiently find the range of valid indices for `j` using binary search (`bisect_left` and `bisect_right`). This approach ensures that we can count the number of fair pairs in `O(n log n)` time, which is suitable given the problem constraints.", "estimated_date": 1676160000000}